
---


@startuml

' Define the main classes
class Doctor {
    - name: String
    - address: String
    - phone: String
    - practitionerNumber: Integer
    - signature: Image
}

class Patient {
    - healthNumber: String
    - firstName: String
    - lastName: String
    - dateOfBirth: Date
    - address: String
    - phone: String
}

class Requisition {
    - validityDate: Date
    - tests: List<Test>
    - repetitionInterval: IntervalType
    - repetitionCount: Integer
}

class Test {
    - name: String
    - testGroup: TestGroup
    - duration: Duration
    - isWalkInOnly: Boolean
    - isSampleDropOff: Boolean
}

class Lab {
    - name: String
    - registrationNumber: String
    - address: String
    - businessHours: BusinessHours
    - changeCancellationFee: Double
}

class Appointment {
    - confirmationNumber: String
    - date: Date
    - startTime: Time
    - endTime: Time
    - lab: Lab
    - requisition: Requisition
}

class Result {
    - test: Test
    - resultStatus: ResultStatus (Positive/Negative)
    - report: String
}

class IntervalType {
    <<enumeration>>
    Weekly, Monthly, HalfYearly, Yearly
}

class TestGroup {
    <<enumeration>>
    BloodTest, Ultrasound, XRay, UrineTest, StoolTest
}

class Duration {
    - hours: Integer
}

class BusinessHours {
    - start: Time
    - end: Time
}

class ResultStatus {
    <<enumeration>>
    Positive, Negative
}

' Associations
Doctor "1" -- "0..*" Requisition : creates
Requisition "1" -- "1" Doctor : signedBy
Requisition "1" -- "1" Patient : forPatient
Requisition "1" -- "0..*" Test : includes
Test "1" -- "1" TestGroup : belongsTo
Test "1" -- "1" Duration : hasDuration
Appointment "1" -- "1" Lab : atLab
Appointment "1" -- "1" Requisition : forRequisition
Test "1" -- "0..*" Result : hasResult
Patient "1" -- "0..*" Appointment : makesAppointments
Lab "1" -- "1" BusinessHours : hasBusinessHours
Lab "1" -- "0..*" Appointment : hostsAppointments
@enduml

---

### 📌 Notes on the Diagram:

- **Doctor**: Can create multiple requisitions. Must provide identity info and digital signature.
- **Patient**: Has a unique health number and can be assigned requisitions by doctors.
- **Requisition**: A group of tests from the same `TestGroup`. Can have a repetition pattern.
- **Test**: Defined by lab, grouped into categories like blood, x-ray, etc.
- **Lab**: Provides location and scheduling info. All labs are always open with fixed hours.
- **Appointment**: One-time only for repeated requisitions. Confirmed with lab details.
- **Result**: Each test has one or more results (e.g., positive/negative) and reports.
- **Enumerations**: Used for intervals, test groups, and result statuses for consistency.

